OL,6,F"As with all deaths in custody, this
OL,7,Fwill be investigated by the Prisons
OL,8,Fand Probation Ombudsman and the cause
OL,9,Fof death is for the coroner to
OL,10,Fdetermine."
OL,12,FHe is believed to have died from
OL,13,Fnatural causes.
OL,15,FEarlier this month, Parc Prison's
OL,16,Fdirector Heather Whitehead left by
OL,17,Fmutual agreement following 10 sudden
OL,18,Finmate deaths in just over three
OL,19,Fmonths - with a number of them
OL,20,Fbelieved to be substance-related - and
OL,21,Fdisorder at the prison.
